humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that the patient has no metastatic carcinoma in sentinel lymph nodes (pSN0 (0/2)) and all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma. Therefore, based on New Rules 10 and 11, the N stage is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The pathology report indicates that the tumor classification is pSN0 (0/2), which means that there is no evidence of cancer in the sentinel lymph node(s) (0 out of 2 nodes examined had cancer). Therefore, the N stage for this patient is N0, indicating no regional lymph node involvement.
